content.step1: Preheat oven to 350°F. Grease two 9-inch round pans with butter, dust with cocoa powder. Mix 2 cups flour, 2 cups sugar, ¾ cup cocoa, 2 teaspoons baking powder, 1½ teaspoons baking soda, 1 teaspoon salt in large bowl.
content.step2: Add 2 eggs, 1 cup milk, ½ cup vegetable oil, 2 teaspoons vanilla to dry ingredients. Beat with electric mixer on medium speed for 2 minutes until smooth and well combined.
content.step3: Carefully stir in 1 cup boiling coffee until batter is thin and glossy. This enhances chocolate flavor and creates tender crumb. Divide batter evenly between prepared pans.
content.step4: Bake for 30-35 minutes until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pans for 10 minutes, then turn onto wire racks to cool completely.
content.step5: For frosting, beat 1 cup softened butter until creamy. Add 3½ cups powdered sugar, ¾ cup cocoa, ½ cup milk, 2 teaspoons vanilla. Beat until fluffy.
content.step6: Place one cake layer on plate. Spread with frosting. Top with second layer. Frost top and sides. Decorate with chocolate shavings or sprinkles. Slice into 8 pieces.
